title: Gilgo Beach murder suspect in court as his adult children 'cry themselves to sleep'
description: A US architect charged with murdering three women and suspected of killing a fourth has appeared in court - as his estranged wife said the pair's adult children "cry themselves to sleep".

title: Barbenheimer backlash as Warner Bros regrets 'insensitive' social media posts
description: While Barbenheimer has taken much of the world by storm, the contrast between the two films is causing a stir in Japan where it has been dubbed insensitive.

title: World's most popular YouTube star sues fast food company over 'revolting' burger
description: The world's most popular YouTube star is suing the company behind his fast food chain after fans called the food "low quality" and "inedible".

title: Uber records first ever operating profit
description: Uber has recorded the first operating profit in its history, after trips rose by more than a fifth in the last year.

title: Iran announces nationwide shutdown due to soaring heat
description: Iran has announced a nationwide shutdown due to "unprecedented heat".

title: Lionesses roar through to World Cup knockouts after dominant 6-1 win over China
description: England's Lionesses have reached the knock-out stages of the Women's World Cup after a dominant 6-1 win against China in Adelaide.

title: Could Etsy sellers boycott the platform because of its reserve system?
description: Some sellers on the online marketplace platform Etsy are seeing their takings frozen for extended periods of time - leaving them struggling to trade in the midst of the cost of living crisis.

title: China limits drone exports over fears they are being used in Ukraine conflict
description: China is to limit the export of long-range drones over fears they are being converted for military use in Ukraine.

title: Expat guilty of wife's mercy killing visits her grave for first time after prison release
description: A British pensioner who killed his terminally ill wife in Cyprus to end her suffering has visited her grave for the first time the day after being freed from prison.

title: Yazidi genocide by Islamic State ranked alongside Holocaust after UK recognition
description: Crimes of genocide were committed by Islamic State militants against an ancient religious community in Iraq and Syria, the UK has acknowledged.

title: China v England latest as Lionesses seek to seal Women's World Cup progress
Why Venice could feature on a danger list of heritage sites
description: Venice is under threat of being added to a danger list of heritage sites over the impact of mass tourism and climate change on the city.

title: Mali and Burkina Faso threaten war over plans for military intervention in Niger
description: Mali and Burkina Faso have warned other West African nations that military intervention in Niger will be considered a declaration of warfare against them.

title: 16 construction workers killed as crane collapses while new bridge is built
description: At least 16 construction workers were killed and several others feared trapped after a crane collapsed during the building of a bridge in India.

title: Aung San Suu Kyi receives partial pardon from Myanmar's military junta but to stay under house arrest
description: Myanmar's junta has pardoned ousted civilian leader Aung San Suu Kyi for some of the offences she denies - more than two years after she was detained as part of a military coup.

title: Donald Trump facing new charges over efforts to overturn 2020 election result
description: Donald Trump is facing more criminal charges as part of an investigation into efforts to overturn the 2020 election result and the 6 January storming of the US Capitol building.

title: At least 11 dead as heavy rains from Typhoon Doksuri batter Beijing
description: At least 11 people have died in Beijing after one of the strongest storms to hit the country in years.

title: At least 20 dead and 27 missing as heavy rains from Typhoon Doksuri batter Beijing
description: At least 20 people have died in Beijing after one of the strongest storms to hit northern China in over a decade.
